WEBVTT

00:02.263 --> 00:05.309
[ RKCB's "Baptize" playing ]

00:05.309 --> 00:08.312
♪♪

00:23.632 --> 00:26.983
♪ There's something about
the way you comfort me ♪

00:26.983 --> 00:28.376
Hi.

00:28.376 --> 00:30.204
Hey. How you doing?

00:30.204 --> 00:31.466
I'm doing okay.
How are you doing?

00:31.466 --> 00:33.033
Good.

00:33.033 --> 00:34.730
Mmm.

00:34.730 --> 00:37.298
♪ Showing me love between
your faded sheet ♪

00:39.256 --> 00:43.086
♪ And I know now that
I want you ♪

00:43.086 --> 00:46.307
♪ Let's not make this
complicated ♪

00:46.307 --> 00:48.004
♪ We don't want this love
to break ♪

00:48.004 --> 00:51.486
♪ But I can't stop
from falling through ♪

00:51.486 --> 00:53.705
What?Did you just
look at your watch?

00:53.705 --> 00:55.490
[ Chuckles ] No.

00:55.490 --> 00:58.493
I'm not touching you until you
take that watch off.

00:58.493 --> 01:01.800
I'm gonna take off
more than my watch.

01:01.800 --> 01:06.414
♪ Feel you washing over me ♪

01:06.414 --> 01:09.069
♪ I don't need to hide it ♪

01:09.069 --> 01:11.810
♪ I love it when you,
love it when you ♪

01:11.810 --> 01:17.207
♪ Baptize me ♪

01:17.207 --> 01:22.386
♪♪

01:22.386 --> 01:25.737
♪ They say I'm in denial ♪

01:25.737 --> 01:29.437
♪ I just can't let go ♪

01:29.437 --> 01:32.396
♪ I don't care what people say ♪

01:32.396 --> 01:35.747
♪ I'm doing all I know ♪

01:35.747 --> 01:39.186
♪ I think of you, my love ♪

01:39.186 --> 01:42.972
♪ And I close my eyes ♪

01:42.972 --> 01:46.628
♪ And I can feel you here ♪

01:46.628 --> 01:49.370
♪ For one more night ♪

01:49.370 --> 01:50.980
Ugh. [ Sniffles ]

01:50.980 --> 01:53.548
I'm terrible. I'm terrible!

01:53.548 --> 01:55.898
[ Music track stops ]No, it's feeling really good.
Let's just go another one.

01:55.898 --> 01:57.378
[ Feedback whines ]

01:57.378 --> 01:59.206
I can't get it poppin'.

02:00.946 --> 02:03.732
What's in the bottle, Alicia?

02:03.732 --> 02:08.258
[ Exhales ] H2O, like it says.

02:08.258 --> 02:11.653
Russian water.

02:11.653 --> 02:14.612
Andy, Andy, let her be.

02:14.612 --> 02:16.571
[ Grunts ]

02:16.571 --> 02:17.963
Give me that bottle, Alicia.

02:17.963 --> 02:20.096
No!Give it to me.

02:20.096 --> 02:21.445
Don't you dare!Give it to me, Alicia.
Give it to me. Give it to me.

02:21.445 --> 02:23.404
No! Let -- No!Come on!

02:23.404 --> 02:26.711
You're not an artist! You don't
know what an artist needs!

02:26.711 --> 02:28.626
[ Cap clinks ]

02:28.626 --> 02:31.238
Talent. Inspiration. Maybe just
a littlebit of discipline.

02:31.238 --> 02:33.414
But a liter of vodka
at 11:00 in the morning?

02:33.414 --> 02:35.329
What are you doing?

02:35.329 --> 02:37.244
[ Crying ] You don't own me.
That's what Normandy would say.

02:37.244 --> 02:38.810
Just take all that pain

02:38.810 --> 02:40.899
and put it into the music
where it belongs.

02:40.899 --> 02:43.163
Look, let's -- let's go again.
Give her an auto-tune track.

02:43.163 --> 02:45.121
[ Grunts ] Yousing it.

02:45.121 --> 02:47.689
[ Headphones thud ]Come on, stop being a baby,
Alicia.

02:47.689 --> 02:49.517
I hate you so muchright now!

02:49.517 --> 02:51.171
Uhh! Uhh!Stop!

02:51.171 --> 02:53.999
Leave me alone! Ugh!

02:53.999 --> 02:57.481
Look, that is the grief talking.
Use it!

02:57.481 --> 03:01.659
Damn! [ Exhales sharply ]

03:01.659 --> 03:05.881
Nice work, Andy.

03:05.881 --> 03:08.927
♪♪

03:17.893 --> 03:20.287
I just wanna tell y'all...

03:20.287 --> 03:21.984
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

03:21.984 --> 03:26.118
...that I'm free today
'cause I put my trust in God.

03:26.118 --> 03:29.383
I accepted Jesus
as my co-pilot.

03:29.383 --> 03:32.037
I lost my brother,

03:32.037 --> 03:34.301
a man I loved like a brother

03:34.301 --> 03:37.652
since were little kids
in the East Bay.

03:37.652 --> 03:42.744
But nothing can bring him back.

03:42.744 --> 03:45.964
And then to have
the whole world thinking

03:45.964 --> 03:48.228
that I did that to him?

03:48.228 --> 03:52.014
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

03:52.014 --> 03:54.973
We'd like to thank
the Acting D.A., Martin Reardon,

03:54.973 --> 03:58.673
for his courage in showing
a commitment to justice,

03:58.673 --> 04:00.370
not politics.

04:00.370 --> 04:02.720
We've needed change
like this for years.

04:02.720 --> 04:04.418
Maybe now
we can finally break

04:04.418 --> 04:05.854
the police department's
choke hold

04:05.854 --> 04:07.247
on the D.A.'s office.

04:07.247 --> 04:09.814
Choke hold? [ Chuckles ] Billy...

04:09.814 --> 04:11.338
why'd you run?

04:11.338 --> 04:13.253
I was scared.

04:13.253 --> 04:15.777
Because innocence doesn't keep
black men breathing in America.

04:15.777 --> 04:19.128
Yeah, you saw how that cop shot
the guy he thoughtwas me.

04:19.128 --> 04:22.436
Billy panicked. He was trying
to stay alive.

04:22.436 --> 04:24.655
Woman: We're coming to you live
from the Oakland office...

04:24.655 --> 04:26.396
Hildy: Shit. ...of Nathan Woodward,
the attorney --

04:26.396 --> 04:28.311
[ Sighs ][ Turns off TV ]

04:28.311 --> 04:29.573
They're all scum
on that side of the aisle.

04:29.573 --> 04:31.836
Woodward's a punk.

04:31.836 --> 04:34.186
Mm, well, if Siletti hadn't
run over that civilian --

04:34.186 --> 04:36.276
He hit her.
He didn't run over her.

04:36.276 --> 04:38.103
Just to be accurate
for the record.Okay, but dead no matter what.

04:38.103 --> 04:40.192
I mean, the point is, Siletti
would've charged to the max...

04:40.192 --> 04:41.803
Navarro: Right....and -- and then he would've
kept him inside,

04:41.803 --> 04:43.979
and we would have time it to --
to build our case.

04:43.979 --> 04:47.112
Right, but outside, Billy has
room to make mistakes, guys.

04:47.112 --> 04:48.549
That's how we're gonna
take him down.

04:48.549 --> 04:51.421
Mm-hmm. That's all we got.Yep.

04:51.421 --> 04:55.164
You need to be 100% safe.
110%.

04:55.164 --> 04:57.427
That means you drive under
the speed limit.

04:57.427 --> 05:00.300
[ Sighs ]You don't contact anybody
of interest. You get me?

05:00.300 --> 05:02.040
You stay close to home
with Rainelle.

05:02.040 --> 05:05.000
You behave like you are strapped
with an ankle monitor.

05:05.000 --> 05:08.612
Because they will be
watching you, for a while.

05:08.612 --> 05:12.224
But you are
a waste of scarce resources

05:12.224 --> 05:15.967
if you don't
produce results.

05:15.967 --> 05:17.926
Let's give Sunday thanks
for tight budgets.

05:17.926 --> 05:19.754
Nathan...

05:19.754 --> 05:21.103
I hope you don't charge
by the word

05:21.103 --> 05:22.844
'cause you use so many.

05:22.844 --> 05:26.891
[ Chuckles ] No, ma'am.

05:26.891 --> 05:28.153
All right.

05:28.153 --> 05:29.764
Thanks, bro.Mm-hmm.

05:29.764 --> 05:32.114
[ Door squeaks ]

05:33.942 --> 05:36.945
You keep showing up, Mario.
You just keep showing up.

05:36.945 --> 05:38.425
What do you want?

05:38.425 --> 05:41.515
Still my office,
my chairs, my desk.

05:41.515 --> 05:45.388
Can you get to the point,
please? One of us is busy.

05:45.388 --> 05:46.781
Eddie Moss.

05:51.307 --> 05:53.309
What about him?

05:53.309 --> 05:57.444
I, uh, caught his name on your
witness list in the rape trial.

05:57.444 --> 05:59.576
Yeah, well, the defendant
couldn't resist bragging to him

05:59.576 --> 06:01.317
when they were in jail
together.

06:01.317 --> 06:02.753
College don't make you
smart.

06:02.753 --> 06:04.538
Now without the informant,

06:04.538 --> 06:06.322
all you have is
"he said, she said," right?

06:06.322 --> 06:08.193
A college kid versus
a paid escort.

06:08.193 --> 06:09.934
That's weak for rape.

06:09.934 --> 06:11.196
And I told you that back when
you charged, remember?

06:11.196 --> 06:12.589
Then we got lucky, I guess.
It happens.

06:12.589 --> 06:15.331
Can you put that down,
please?

06:15.331 --> 06:17.986
You planted the informant,
Marty, to shore up your case.

06:17.986 --> 06:21.206
You have lost your mind.
I did no such thing.

06:21.206 --> 06:23.295
Afteryour defendant already
had an attorney,

06:23.295 --> 06:26.734
thus the right it remain silent,
which you violated.

06:26.734 --> 06:29.127
The defense is gonna shred you
like pulled pork.

06:29.127 --> 06:30.825
Moss' name is
in our database --

06:30.825 --> 06:32.479
There's no outside access
to our database.

06:32.479 --> 06:33.915
It won't pass
as a coincidence

06:33.915 --> 06:36.308
that a snitch
in so many other cases

06:36.308 --> 06:38.441
wound up next to your
chatty defendant in custody.

06:41.226 --> 06:43.794
Well, I'm going to assume

06:43.794 --> 06:45.927
that if I didn't know anything
about that,

06:45.927 --> 06:49.147
neither will
the kid's attorney.

06:49.147 --> 06:50.584
You need to make a deal,
Marty.

06:50.584 --> 06:52.412
[ Laughs ]
That's not your call anymore.

06:52.412 --> 06:54.979
Oh, so you're willing
to benefit from perjury,

06:54.979 --> 06:56.416
obstruction of justice,

06:56.416 --> 06:58.113
violation
of constitutional rights --

06:58.113 --> 07:00.245
Mario! Mario, this kid
is a monster.

07:00.245 --> 07:02.509
Of course he is!

07:02.509 --> 07:05.903
And you're trying to protect
the victim. I get it.

07:05.903 --> 07:09.516
But I would hate to see you ruin
your career over this, Marty.

07:09.516 --> 07:11.213
I mean,
you're too good a lawyer.

07:11.213 --> 07:12.693
[ Sighs ] This...

07:12.693 --> 07:14.695
[ Taps finger ]...is mydesk.

07:14.695 --> 07:16.740
You are sitting
in one of mychairs.

07:16.740 --> 07:18.960
Do you get that? Is that
resonating with you?

07:18.960 --> 07:21.179
You are never coming back,
Mario, okay?

07:21.179 --> 07:23.225
So get used to it, okay?

07:23.225 --> 07:25.967
You don't take my good advice,
you will lose the case.

07:25.967 --> 07:28.230
You will be publicly humiliated.

07:28.230 --> 07:30.275
You were the one
who was in charge.

07:30.275 --> 07:33.148
Y-You!
You are such a hypocrite.

07:33.148 --> 07:35.324
I believed in the integrity
of my subordinates.

07:35.324 --> 07:36.717
Apparently, I was wrong.

07:36.717 --> 07:38.893
You know what?

07:38.893 --> 07:41.156
You used to care about
the victims.

07:41.156 --> 07:42.810
Hmm? You remember that?

07:42.810 --> 07:44.072
Back before you went
and put yourself

07:44.072 --> 07:45.682
on the wrong side
of the aisle.

07:45.682 --> 07:46.944
Youdid that to yourself.

07:46.944 --> 07:48.424
I am living proof

07:48.424 --> 07:49.904
that not every defendant
is guilty as charged.

07:49.904 --> 07:52.602
[ Chuckles ]

07:52.602 --> 07:55.083
Well...I came as a friend.

07:55.083 --> 07:57.607
[ Laughs ]
We were never friends.

07:57.607 --> 08:00.871
Oh, now you're just trying
to be mean.

08:00.871 --> 08:03.352
At least I won't feel sorry
for you when you lose, Marty.

08:06.486 --> 08:09.271
Good luck in court.

08:09.271 --> 08:12.404
♪♪

08:12.404 --> 08:14.319
Hi.
Hey.

08:14.319 --> 08:16.496
You okay?Yeah, I'm okay.

08:16.496 --> 08:18.585
Are youokay?[ Chuckles ] I think so.

08:18.585 --> 08:20.064
[ Chuckles ]

08:20.064 --> 08:21.631
Oh. [ Sighs ]

08:21.631 --> 08:23.328
All right, Billy James
definitely had enough cash

08:23.328 --> 08:24.808
to skip town.

08:24.808 --> 08:26.375
What was he waiting on?

08:26.375 --> 08:28.290
Mm.
Or who?

08:28.290 --> 08:30.161
Hey. Uh...Uh, my guess is Daphne.

08:30.161 --> 08:33.991
[ Chuckles ]
...my guess would be Daphne.[ Chuckles ]

08:33.991 --> 08:35.819
So we sit on them?

08:35.819 --> 08:37.081
Right.Well, yeah, I mean,
if -- if we're right,

08:37.081 --> 08:38.561
one of them's gonna
make a move.

08:38.561 --> 08:40.215
Terry: It'll just be
a matter of time.

08:40.215 --> 08:43.697
Yeah.
Lust makes you stupid.

08:43.697 --> 08:46.700
♪♪

08:58.668 --> 09:01.758
[ Door creaks ]

09:01.758 --> 09:06.284
Alicia?

09:06.284 --> 09:07.895
It's me.

09:07.895 --> 09:10.985
[ Keys jangle ]

09:10.985 --> 09:12.856
[ Jacket thuds ]

09:12.856 --> 09:14.858
[ Keys jangle ]

09:14.858 --> 09:16.251
[ Keys clatter ]

09:16.251 --> 09:18.253
Babe?

09:18.253 --> 09:21.299
♪♪

09:23.214 --> 09:24.564
Alicia?

09:24.564 --> 09:28.393
[ Keypad beeping ]

09:28.393 --> 09:30.308
Honey?

09:34.095 --> 09:38.403
[ Sighs ]

09:38.403 --> 09:39.970
[ Doorknob rattles ]

09:39.970 --> 09:41.493
Baby.

09:41.493 --> 09:43.104
[ Doorknob rattles ]

09:43.104 --> 09:44.496
[ Sighs ]

09:44.496 --> 09:46.411
[ Click ]

09:46.411 --> 09:49.066
I'm comin' in.

09:49.066 --> 09:51.199
[ Door creaks ]

09:51.199 --> 09:53.767
Alicia?

09:53.767 --> 09:55.420
Alicia!

09:55.420 --> 09:57.509
Alicia, baby. no.
No, no, no. Come on.

09:57.509 --> 09:58.989
Alicia. Come on, baby.
[ Grunts ] Come on.

09:58.989 --> 10:02.166
Alicia, wake up. Wake up!
Wake up.

10:02.166 --> 10:05.039
Hold on. [ Grunts ]

10:05.039 --> 10:07.737
Stay with me. Come on. Come on.

10:07.737 --> 10:09.434
Get you out of here.
You're okay.

10:09.434 --> 10:11.654
What have you done?
What have you done?

10:11.654 --> 10:15.527
Come on. No, no, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no. Come on.

10:19.793 --> 10:21.403
Come on, one shot, man.

10:21.403 --> 10:25.494
I'm just doing my job here.
Okay? Come on.

10:25.494 --> 10:26.887
-Did you not hear me?
-Man: Back! Back!

10:26.887 --> 10:30.586
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:33.284 --> 10:36.679
Back up! Back up!

10:36.679 --> 10:39.290
Out of the way!
Make some room!

10:39.290 --> 10:42.119
[ Female reporter
shouts indistinctly ]

10:42.119 --> 10:44.774
[ Reporters shouting at once ]

10:48.125 --> 10:50.084
Andrew: No, uh, I don't know
what she took.

10:50.084 --> 10:51.955
it could've been anything,
e-everything.

10:51.955 --> 10:54.088
Okay, and who are you, exactly?I'm her attorney.

10:54.088 --> 10:57.134
Look, I-I-I need to be with her.
Can -- can I go with you guys?

10:57.134 --> 10:58.745
I just...Man: Get in the back.

10:58.745 --> 11:00.660
[ Indistinct conversations ]

11:00.660 --> 11:02.444
[ Engine starts,
ambulance doors close ]

11:09.146 --> 11:10.539
[ Siren wailing ]Hildy: Cozy.

11:10.539 --> 11:11.975
Terry: [ Chuckles ]

11:11.975 --> 11:15.109
Whoa.

11:15.109 --> 11:16.545
What happened in here?

11:16.545 --> 11:18.242
Girl's a slob.

11:18.242 --> 11:21.637
Probably never picked up
anything in her entire life.

11:21.637 --> 11:23.378
Oh. [ Groans ]

11:23.378 --> 11:24.858
These are worth more than
my mortgage payment.

11:24.858 --> 11:26.686
[ Shoe thuds ][ Chuckles ]

11:26.686 --> 11:28.557
Normandy had to deal
with all this?

11:28.557 --> 11:32.387
Well, her house, her rules,
her hot bod.

11:38.741 --> 11:41.135
Okay.

11:41.135 --> 11:42.919
[ Door squeaks ]

11:44.355 --> 11:46.183
[ Camera shutter clicking ]This guy's medicine cabinet

11:46.183 --> 11:48.142
looks like it belongs
to an old man.

11:48.142 --> 11:50.361
Well, that's what Burnside said,
right?

11:50.361 --> 11:52.146
[ Camera shutter clicks ]Uh, all prescribed by
the team doctor.

11:52.146 --> 11:53.974
Dr. Feel-Good.

11:53.974 --> 11:56.106
Dr. Feel-Good-Enough-to-Play.Mm.

11:56.106 --> 11:58.369
Ooh. Question.Mm-hmm?

11:58.369 --> 12:01.285
Why would a star athlete
in the prime of his life

12:01.285 --> 12:02.591
need beta blockers?

12:02.591 --> 12:04.680
[ Pills rattle ]

12:04.680 --> 12:06.421
Although, if this crazy chick
were my girl,

12:06.421 --> 12:08.292
my blood pressure would
spike, too.

12:08.292 --> 12:09.641
Those the same doctor?

12:09.641 --> 12:11.948
Uh, no.
This one's Jack Kaplan.

12:11.948 --> 12:13.733
Kaplan.

12:13.733 --> 12:15.822
Okay.

12:15.822 --> 12:17.214
Got it. Pacific Heights.

12:17.214 --> 12:18.694
Ooh. Fancy.

12:18.694 --> 12:20.783
Cardiologist.
Stanford-educated.

12:20.783 --> 12:22.132
Guy's the real deal.

12:22.132 --> 12:23.394
Address? Number?

12:23.394 --> 12:24.744
Yeah. Saved.

12:24.744 --> 12:26.920
You good?

12:26.920 --> 12:28.704
I'm good.

12:32.055 --> 12:34.362
Hildy: Why was he taking
a beta blocker?

12:34.362 --> 12:38.279
I want to help, but I cannot
disclose medical information

12:38.279 --> 12:41.891
without my patient's consent,
which he cannot give me anymore.

12:41.891 --> 12:44.372
All right, so as Normandy's
primary physician,

12:44.372 --> 12:46.635
you were acting
in his best interest, correct?

12:46.635 --> 12:47.984
Yes, of course.

12:47.984 --> 12:49.986
So, Dr. Kaplan,
why stop there?

12:49.986 --> 12:53.729
I would think he would expect
you to cooperate with us.

12:53.729 --> 12:56.863
This isn't a breach

12:56.863 --> 12:59.474
if you're presupposing
Normandy's consent

12:59.474 --> 13:02.520
to solve this murder.

13:02.520 --> 13:05.175
You're doing nothing wrong,
sir.

13:05.175 --> 13:07.308
[ Sighs ]

13:07.308 --> 13:10.702
He came to me experiencing
atrial fibrillation,

13:10.702 --> 13:14.010
specifically,
a fast, irregular heartbeat.

13:14.010 --> 13:17.971
I prescribed Atenolol
to slow down the heart rate.

13:17.971 --> 13:20.582
A.F. is a manageable condition

13:20.582 --> 13:22.453
if there are
no complicating factors.

13:22.453 --> 13:25.413
Like an aneurysm?

13:25.413 --> 13:27.589
We saw the autopsy reports.

13:27.589 --> 13:29.243
You knew about the aneurysm.

13:29.243 --> 13:30.548
Of course.

13:30.548 --> 13:32.246
It showed up
in the echocardiogram.

13:32.246 --> 13:35.162
I was monitoring it for --
for any growth.

13:35.162 --> 13:37.468
But early surgery

13:37.468 --> 13:40.820
d-doesn't bring
long-term survival advantage.

13:40.820 --> 13:43.953
Did you discuss his condition
with the team doctor?

13:43.953 --> 13:46.434
Normandy refused to let me.
He...

13:46.434 --> 13:49.350
he didn't want anyone to know,
not even his own family.

13:49.350 --> 13:51.134
It wasn't a medical decision.

13:51.134 --> 13:52.744
In your opinion,

13:52.744 --> 13:53.963
do you think Normandy put
his life in jeopardy

13:53.963 --> 13:55.617
by playing football?

13:55.617 --> 13:59.273
A cardiac event cannot
be predicted.

13:59.273 --> 14:02.450
Watchful waiting makes sense
for the typical patient his age.

14:02.450 --> 14:05.496
But Normandy wasn't typical.
Violence was his profession.

14:05.496 --> 14:08.673
The risk was higher for him.
of course,

14:08.673 --> 14:10.806
as I fully informed him.

14:10.806 --> 14:14.897
But patients have the right
to make up their own minds.

14:14.897 --> 14:18.161
The irony is, it -- it wasn't
the cardiac condition

14:18.161 --> 14:19.946
that killed him.

14:19.946 --> 14:24.428
Just...a man with a gun.

14:24.428 --> 14:26.866
What a waste.

14:26.866 --> 14:29.651
Why was Normandy willing
to roll the dice like that?

14:29.651 --> 14:31.435
Just for the money?

14:31.435 --> 14:33.220
It's hard to give up
that kind of stardom, you know?

14:33.220 --> 14:35.222
Now who are you when you used
to be Normandy Parker?

14:35.222 --> 14:37.311
Yeah, making $14 mil a year
on the field.

14:37.311 --> 14:39.052
That'd be, what?
Like, a hundred years for us?

14:39.052 --> 14:42.185
No, 50, after he pays
his taxes.[ Laughs ]

14:42.185 --> 14:44.579
Well, I guess he has a big nut
to cover though, right?

14:44.579 --> 14:46.450
I mean, between the wife
and the house and the kids

14:46.450 --> 14:49.453
and his boys, his toys,
his personal payroll.

14:49.453 --> 14:50.933
Maybe he hadto play.

14:50.933 --> 14:53.283
We'll need a forensics
accountant. Doctor what?

14:53.283 --> 14:55.416
Adler. I'll call her.

14:55.416 --> 14:57.809
All right. Then you two of you
go relieve Molk and Navarro.

14:57.809 --> 14:59.202
Too much close time together,

14:59.202 --> 15:00.769
they start to act like
rats in a cage.

15:00.769 --> 15:04.642
[ Laughs ] Yeah.Yes, sir.

15:04.642 --> 15:08.081
Terry. A minute?

15:08.081 --> 15:09.560
Sure.

15:09.560 --> 15:14.348
[ Blinds clatter ]

15:14.348 --> 15:18.613
You and Hildy
are my strongest team.

15:18.613 --> 15:21.181
I can't have that jeopardized
by pheromones.

15:21.181 --> 15:23.096
Oh --
Don't interrupt me.

15:23.096 --> 15:25.750
I'm talking to you
as a friend here.

15:25.750 --> 15:27.752
If there's something going on
between the two of you,

15:27.752 --> 15:29.624
or about to go on --

15:29.624 --> 15:33.367
and I'm not asking
for an answer -- it stops now,

15:33.367 --> 15:37.066
or one of you needs
to transfer out.

15:37.066 --> 15:39.808
Uh, there's no departmental
policy on this.

15:39.808 --> 15:43.159
Yeah, well, there is in
my command. I have the option.

15:43.159 --> 15:45.422
Look, I-I can't have
my detectives

15:45.422 --> 15:47.120
multitracking on the job.

15:47.120 --> 15:48.730
You screw each other,
you screw the work.

15:48.730 --> 15:50.253
Am I being clear enough?

15:50.253 --> 15:53.082
Yes, sir.

15:53.082 --> 15:55.128
You know you're next in line
for my desk,

15:55.128 --> 15:57.391
if and when I make a move,
right?

15:57.391 --> 15:59.480
What happens to Hildy then?

15:59.480 --> 16:01.656
You have an ongoing relationship
with a subordinate?

16:01.656 --> 16:04.093
Or a bad history?

16:04.093 --> 16:06.182
Either way, it's a mess.

16:06.182 --> 16:08.097
All right,
this has to go away now, Terry,

16:08.097 --> 16:10.621
or I'll let
the two of you decide

16:10.621 --> 16:15.061
which one of you leaves
the division.[ Sighs ]

16:15.061 --> 16:18.455
The job comes first
while I'm in charge.

16:18.455 --> 16:20.370
Work it out.

16:22.503 --> 16:25.767
Are you finished, sir?

16:25.767 --> 16:27.508
I'm not the problem.

16:27.508 --> 16:29.292
There isno problem.

16:32.339 --> 16:35.081
[ Blinds rattle ]

16:36.952 --> 16:38.649
♪♪

16:42.523 --> 16:44.916
♪♪

16:44.916 --> 16:46.744
Oh, "retirement's"
a beautiful word.

16:46.744 --> 16:48.181
You're depressing me, Molk.

16:48.181 --> 16:51.010
Ah, nice.Aw, man.

16:51.010 --> 16:52.707
[ Sighs deeply ]No, look, look.

16:52.707 --> 16:54.448
Mm-hmm?No, what I'm saying is --
is that

16:54.448 --> 16:56.711
as opposed to buying a bar
or a business,

16:56.711 --> 16:58.104
what you do is you buy --
buy the building

16:58.104 --> 16:59.627
that they're in, right?Mm-hmm.

16:59.627 --> 17:01.411
And then you lease it back
to them.Mm.

17:01.411 --> 17:02.847
See what I'm saying? So then
you get into real estate.

17:02.847 --> 17:04.240
Now that's where you
stretch your...

17:04.240 --> 17:05.894
[ Fabric rustles ]...stretch your pension.

17:05.894 --> 17:09.158
My p--
58's a long way off.Used to be.

17:09.158 --> 17:12.118
[ Exhales sharply ] Sometimes,
I hate you, you know?

17:12.118 --> 17:13.554
[ Knock on window ]Yes!

17:13.554 --> 17:15.164
Hey!

17:15.164 --> 17:16.513
Terry:
All right, what's going on?

17:16.513 --> 17:17.862
Hello.Fresh babysitters. Thank you!

17:17.862 --> 17:19.342
Yeah.[ Terry laughs ]

17:19.342 --> 17:21.083
Stakeouts are a test
of mental discipline.

17:21.083 --> 17:22.737
Mm-hmm, and bladder control.

17:22.737 --> 17:24.130
Smells ripe in here.Navarro: Mm-hmm.

17:24.130 --> 17:26.958
Has Billy budged?Oh, sure, at, uh...

17:26.958 --> 17:29.483
9:12, he came out to water
the roses.

17:29.483 --> 17:31.354
At 11:34, he carried out
the trash.

17:31.354 --> 17:34.488
At 2:10, he took grandma
on a short postprandial walk --

17:34.488 --> 17:36.272
Molk's word of the day.You're welcome.

17:36.272 --> 17:37.752
Any visitors?

17:37.752 --> 17:39.406
Mnh-mnh.
Grandma must not approve.

17:39.406 --> 17:41.060
On the positive side,
Molk's convinced me

17:41.060 --> 17:42.626
to dump my mutual funds
and buy real estate.

17:42.626 --> 17:44.802
Good.I just said
you should diversify.

17:44.802 --> 17:46.630
You're not listening.Yeah, diversify my nuts, man.

17:46.630 --> 17:48.415
[ Keys jangle ]I am not interested
in your nuts, man.

17:48.415 --> 17:50.547
Car's around the corner.
All right.All right. Okay.

17:50.547 --> 17:52.288
I wish you would listen to me.
I'm just talking about your --Bye, guys.

17:52.288 --> 17:54.160
Look, I mean,
I have experiences --Navarro: Later.

17:54.160 --> 17:55.596
These are important decisions.

17:55.596 --> 17:57.119
[ Car door closes ]Bye. See ya.

17:57.119 --> 18:00.296
What does "prandial" mean?No clue.

18:00.296 --> 18:02.081
Okay, why are you sharing this
with me?

18:02.081 --> 18:03.995
As an act of conscience.[ Scoffs ]

18:03.995 --> 18:05.649
You know, I'm hurt
that you look surprised.

18:05.649 --> 18:07.521
I am an officer of the court,
same as you, Al.

18:07.521 --> 18:09.392
It's the right thing to do.

18:09.392 --> 18:10.828
You probably even know the young
man's attorney in this case.

18:10.828 --> 18:12.265
Yeah, as a matter of fact.

18:12.265 --> 18:13.788
You don't need to show him
the file.

18:13.788 --> 18:16.051
Which is highly confidential
and probably illegal.

18:16.051 --> 18:18.271
Did you know that
the attorney-client privilege

18:18.271 --> 18:20.142
is the oldest privilege
recognized

18:20.142 --> 18:21.970
by Anglo-American
jurisprudence?

18:21.970 --> 18:23.885
16th century.

18:23.885 --> 18:25.669
[ Chuckles ]
Beautiful, isn't it?

18:25.669 --> 18:28.716
Meaning that I could
pass along a tip

18:28.716 --> 18:31.719
from a protected source --
you.

18:31.719 --> 18:34.374
Public records speak
for themselves...

18:34.374 --> 18:35.766
once somebody knows
where to look.

18:35.766 --> 18:37.551
Wow. Office politics, man.

18:37.551 --> 18:40.206
You people are brutal
with each other.

18:40.206 --> 18:42.512
Reardon doesn't deserve the job.
This isn't personal.

18:42.512 --> 18:44.993
Of course it isn't.[ Chuckles ]

18:44.993 --> 18:46.473
Do you care?

18:46.473 --> 18:48.170
About your motives?
No, not particularly.

18:48.170 --> 18:49.998
Well, you did tell me to plan
for my future.

18:49.998 --> 18:51.478
Is this gonna help our case?

18:51.478 --> 18:53.871
Yes.

18:55.830 --> 18:58.180
So what'd Koto say?

18:58.180 --> 19:00.922
Koto? When?

19:00.922 --> 19:02.837
When he asked you to stay behind
in his office,

19:02.837 --> 19:05.144
and you went in
and closed the door.

19:05.144 --> 19:06.797
[ Laughs ] Oh, my God.

19:06.797 --> 19:09.757
That's such a tell when you do
that head thing.

19:09.757 --> 19:11.019
[ Inhales deeply,
exhales slowly ]

19:11.019 --> 19:12.629
Uh... [ Clears throat ]

19:12.629 --> 19:15.589
He said he thinks
we've gotten, uh, personal.

19:15.589 --> 19:19.070
How?

19:19.070 --> 19:20.811
W-what did you say?

19:20.811 --> 19:22.683
Nothin'.Nothing? You just sat there
in dead silence?

19:22.683 --> 19:24.946
Nothing. I mean,
I listened to him.

19:24.946 --> 19:27.470
I mean, he's a good cop.
He's -- he's observant.

19:29.342 --> 19:33.520
Are we ready to...
go public?

19:33.520 --> 19:35.696
Koto won't let us
work together like that.

19:35.696 --> 19:38.525
What, he'd break up
our partnership?

19:38.525 --> 19:40.657
No, worse.

19:40.657 --> 19:43.312
[ Inhales deeply ]
He said that the two of us...

19:43.312 --> 19:44.922
[ Clears throat ]
...could not continue

19:44.922 --> 19:49.318
working Homicide if we're
together and that, uh...

19:49.318 --> 19:52.278
one of us would have
to transfer.

19:52.278 --> 19:54.410
Wow. That's...
Yeah.

19:54.410 --> 19:56.282
[ Scoffs ] overstepping.

19:56.282 --> 19:59.067
Yeah, it doesn't matter,
'cause...

19:59.067 --> 20:01.025
he's above us
in the chain of command

20:01.025 --> 20:04.246
and, uh, it's his decision,
so...

20:04.246 --> 20:05.943
All right. [ Sighs ]

20:05.943 --> 20:09.164
So I guess we just...

20:09.164 --> 20:10.905
stay deep undercover, yeah?

20:10.905 --> 20:13.908
Mnh-mnh.
I wanna be a couple, baby,

20:13.908 --> 20:19.305
not a...
[ Sighs ] couple of sneaks.

20:19.305 --> 20:22.221
Mm.

20:22.221 --> 20:25.441
Well, you know, you know
you'd have to be the one

20:25.441 --> 20:27.051
to transfer, right? Not me.

20:28.705 --> 20:30.098
Me?

20:33.449 --> 20:35.930
I've worked my ass off
to make Homicide, Terry.

20:35.930 --> 20:37.845
I mean, I did, too.

20:37.845 --> 20:42.415
Yeah, I know you did. But you're
a guy. It's different.

20:42.415 --> 20:45.331
You share the same hormones.
You're welcome in any division.

20:45.331 --> 20:48.290
You could do Vice. You could do
Special Investigations.

20:48.290 --> 20:51.467
So, okay, but I'm --
I'm supposed to transfer down

20:51.467 --> 20:52.773
because you're a woman?

20:52.773 --> 20:54.470
Is that what you're saying?

20:54.470 --> 20:56.559
You know it would be easier
for you than for me.

20:56.559 --> 20:59.127
I'm sorry. I mean,
I wish it wasn't true.

20:59.127 --> 21:01.390
Homicide's everything to me.

21:01.390 --> 21:04.088
It's all I've ever wanted.
It...

21:04.088 --> 21:06.308
I l-- I love this job.

21:06.308 --> 21:09.485
[ Sighs deeply ]
Me, too.

21:09.485 --> 21:11.139
I know, but it's not just
about career for me.

21:11.139 --> 21:12.836
I'm saying...

21:12.836 --> 21:14.447
it's who I am.

21:14.447 --> 21:16.536
[ Sighs ]

21:16.536 --> 21:18.015
It's who we both are.

21:22.672 --> 21:27.503
[ Terry sighs ]

21:27.503 --> 21:29.244
Where does that leave us?

21:31.377 --> 21:33.030
Right now?

21:36.164 --> 21:37.600
On a stakeout.

21:41.082 --> 21:42.605
[ Sighs deeply ]

21:44.912 --> 21:47.523
Woman over P.A.: Dr. Collins,
dial 3-2-1-1.

21:47.523 --> 21:51.310
Dr. Collins, dial 3-2-1-1.

22:06.673 --> 22:09.371
[ Whispers ] Hi, baby.

22:09.371 --> 22:11.547
[ Voice breaks ] Hi, Daddy.

22:11.547 --> 22:14.594
[ Crying ]

22:14.594 --> 22:17.597
I'm here, Ally.

22:17.597 --> 22:19.729
Daddy's here.

22:19.729 --> 22:24.038
[ Inhales sharply ]
I'm so sorry.

22:24.038 --> 22:25.692
I'm so stupid.

22:25.692 --> 22:27.215
No, no, no, no, no, no.

22:27.215 --> 22:28.738
No, no, no, no.[ Inhales sharply ]

22:28.738 --> 22:30.740
[ Whispers ] No, no,
don't even start that.

22:30.740 --> 22:33.177
[ Cries ]

22:33.177 --> 22:36.137
Baby, I'm just glad
you're alive.

22:36.137 --> 22:38.313
You hear me?[ Sniffles ]

22:41.447 --> 22:44.450
Baby, they're asking me...

22:44.450 --> 22:45.842
what you took.

22:48.845 --> 22:52.501
I can't even remember.

22:52.501 --> 22:53.850
How much you took.

22:57.419 --> 22:59.378
Just...

22:59.378 --> 23:01.597
tell them
it wasn't on purpose.

23:03.817 --> 23:05.340
Okay.

23:09.736 --> 23:11.128
[ Inhales deeply ]

23:11.128 --> 23:14.741
You go back to sleep,
baby.

23:14.741 --> 23:16.612
I'm right here.

23:16.612 --> 23:19.354
♪♪

23:19.354 --> 23:22.401
I'm right here.

23:27.101 --> 23:28.842
Let's not just run
with the rumors, people.

23:28.842 --> 23:32.019
Alicia is suffering
from exhaustion and stress

23:32.019 --> 23:33.890
and grief.

23:33.890 --> 23:36.066
And she's overworked herself
with her tribute to Normandy,

23:36.066 --> 23:38.765
which is so important to her
since the tragedy.

23:38.765 --> 23:41.811
This is her last gift to him.
She wants it to be perfect.

23:41.811 --> 23:44.640
Now I don't need to tell you
that she is a perfectionist.

23:44.640 --> 23:46.860
It's not exhaustion.

23:46.860 --> 23:49.253
Why do you lie like that?Paul, not helping.

23:49.253 --> 23:51.386
I'm her father.

23:51.386 --> 23:53.475
Alicia is a drug addict
and an alcoholic

23:53.475 --> 23:55.651
because of the losers like him
living off her,

23:55.651 --> 23:57.436
who lie every time
their lips move.

23:57.436 --> 23:59.046
Isn't that right, Andy?

23:59.046 --> 24:01.178
My daughter was strong
and clean and healthy

24:01.178 --> 24:03.616
until Andy Lippman started
pimping her out for publicity.

24:03.616 --> 24:05.095
Isn't that right, Andy?

24:05.095 --> 24:07.446
You made that happen,
didn't ya?

24:07.446 --> 24:09.056
Why don't you ask Mr. Barnes
about the restraining order

24:09.056 --> 24:10.361
that Alicia
filed against him?

24:10.361 --> 24:12.581
It's all public record.

24:12.581 --> 24:14.278
You were supposed
to protect her!

24:14.278 --> 24:17.456
[ Crowd shouting ]You made that happen!

24:17.456 --> 24:19.066
[ Crowd screaming ]

24:23.374 --> 24:24.898
Hey. Hey.

24:24.898 --> 24:26.639
So Alicia OD'ed?[ Sighs ]

24:26.639 --> 24:28.815
Suicide attempt? Writer's block?
What do you think?

24:28.815 --> 24:30.425
Yeah, I think you don't
play well with others.

24:30.425 --> 24:32.209
That's what I think.

24:32.209 --> 24:33.994
I mean, whatever happened
to our sharing arrangement?

24:33.994 --> 24:35.430
When are yougonna
give mea tip, huh?

24:35.430 --> 24:36.823
Okay, well,
there's some buzz online

24:36.823 --> 24:38.389
that, you know,
Alicia OD'ed out of guilt

24:38.389 --> 24:40.087
for her involvement
in Normandy's murder.

24:40.087 --> 24:41.480
All right, conspiracy theories
don't qualify as tips.

24:41.480 --> 24:42.829
Are you sure she had
no connection

24:42.829 --> 24:44.483
with the murderer at all?

24:44.483 --> 24:47.094
SFPD does not comment
on ongoing investigations.

24:47.094 --> 24:48.878
Come on.
"No comment" sounds so shady.

24:48.878 --> 24:51.185
It just means
you haven't cut her

24:51.185 --> 24:53.404
from your roster of suspects.All right, don't be cute.
It means no comment.

24:53.404 --> 24:54.928
You know, unlike you,
we're looking for facts...

24:54.928 --> 24:57.234
[ Elevator bell dings ]...not headlines.

24:57.234 --> 24:59.106
You're worse than TV news,
you know that?

24:59.106 --> 25:00.716
Excuse me?

25:00.716 --> 25:02.762
Hey, you should slow down
and get it right,

25:02.762 --> 25:05.547
or you're just a joke
with a pretty face,

25:05.547 --> 25:07.593
and I overestimated you.

25:07.593 --> 25:09.638
[ Pushes button ]

25:09.638 --> 25:12.989
Good advice...Jim.

25:14.861 --> 25:18.429
Mr. Moss, how many times
have you testified

25:18.429 --> 25:20.475
for the District Attorney's
office?

25:20.475 --> 25:22.129
This year?Sure.

25:22.129 --> 25:23.696
First time.

25:23.696 --> 25:26.829
And how about last year?Last year was a good year.

25:26.829 --> 25:29.876
I was able to contribute
to justice in three cases.

25:29.876 --> 25:32.443
And how about
the year before that?

25:32.443 --> 25:34.445
Now I'm losing count.

25:34.445 --> 25:35.969
Two or three?

25:35.969 --> 25:38.537
So in the last three years,

25:38.537 --> 25:41.017
you've been a confidential
informant for the D.A.'s office

25:41.017 --> 25:44.020
in at least six,
possibly seven cases

25:44.020 --> 25:45.544
that have gone to court, right?

25:45.544 --> 25:47.502
Yes, ma'am.

25:47.502 --> 25:51.767
Six or possibly seven
total strangers

25:51.767 --> 25:53.900
felt compelled to confess to you
behind bars

25:53.900 --> 25:56.424
without you ever asking a word?

25:56.424 --> 26:00.559
People like to talk to me.
I'm a good listener.

26:00.559 --> 26:04.650
You know how to extract
information, don't you?

26:04.650 --> 26:06.434
Obviously.

26:06.434 --> 26:08.305
In exchange
for valuable consideration

26:08.305 --> 26:11.221
by the D.A.'s office at your
future sentencing, right?

26:11.221 --> 26:13.310
What?

26:13.310 --> 26:17.576
If you help the prosecution,
then the prosecution helps you.

26:17.576 --> 26:20.404
Is that your understanding?

26:20.404 --> 26:23.582
Well, yeah,
because what's right is right,

26:23.582 --> 26:25.671
and what's wrong is...

26:25.671 --> 26:27.368
you know, wrong.

26:27.368 --> 26:31.024
That's what I believe,
same as the D.A.

26:31.024 --> 26:34.070
Your Honor, move to strike
the witness' testimony

26:34.070 --> 26:36.290
in its entirety
as a blatant violation

26:36.290 --> 26:38.205
of the defendant's
Sixth Amendment right

26:38.205 --> 26:39.728
to remain silent

26:39.728 --> 26:41.512
and have counsel present
during questioning,

26:41.512 --> 26:44.515
compounded with the appearance
of gross misconduct

26:44.515 --> 26:45.952
by the D.A.'s office.Your Honor, Your Honor,
unfounded allegation...

26:45.952 --> 26:48.476
Mr. Reardon!...in open court like...

26:48.476 --> 26:51.392
The less you say in support
of your witness, the better,

26:51.392 --> 26:53.307
before we get to the point
where I have to decide

26:53.307 --> 26:55.526
whether you're dishonest
or just thick.

26:55.526 --> 26:56.919
[ Chuckles softly ]

26:56.919 --> 27:01.576
Now I am inclined
to strike the testimony,

27:01.576 --> 27:03.447
but I strongly suspect
that the jury

27:03.447 --> 27:05.754
can deal with it properly
per my instructions.

27:05.754 --> 27:07.669
[ Gallery murmuring ]

27:07.669 --> 27:11.455
You may step down, Mr. Moss.W-what'd I do?

27:11.455 --> 27:14.415
You answered truthfully.
Thank you.

27:14.415 --> 27:18.593
♪♪

27:18.593 --> 27:20.595
[ Whispers ] Excuse me.

27:20.595 --> 27:21.901
Excuse me.

27:23.772 --> 27:25.905
Martin: Your Honor,
may I approach the bench?

27:43.966 --> 27:47.274
[ Woman shouts indistinctly ]

27:47.274 --> 27:50.930
See you next week. Huh?

27:50.930 --> 27:52.192
[ Door creaks ]

27:52.192 --> 27:53.584
What up, boy?Hey.

27:53.584 --> 27:55.369
Here you go.What's up?

27:55.369 --> 27:56.936
[ Speaks indistinctly ]All right, man, you up now.

27:56.936 --> 27:59.460
Billy, Billy, Billy.My man Hal. You can take one?

27:59.460 --> 28:03.116
Be my guest, sir.

28:03.116 --> 28:04.944
[ Sighs ]

28:04.944 --> 28:06.336
One of them days, huh?

28:06.336 --> 28:10.253
Man, you won't believe.

28:10.253 --> 28:12.473
Oh, not too tight, man.
Not too tight.

28:12.473 --> 28:14.257
Hey, hey, it's over now,
crybaby.

28:14.257 --> 28:15.998
[ Both laugh ]

28:15.998 --> 28:17.957
How's Rainelle, Billy?
[ Sighs ]

28:17.957 --> 28:20.350
She's keeping me on my knees.

28:20.350 --> 28:22.309
She's God-fearing,
that's for sure.

28:22.309 --> 28:26.574
[ Combs clink ]How about you? You okay?

28:26.574 --> 28:29.490
It's like I'm in solitary.
You know what I mean?

28:29.490 --> 28:34.234
Nobody wants their name logged
on some damn police report.

28:34.234 --> 28:38.412
They watching you?Please believe.

28:38.412 --> 28:40.109
Yo.Oh.

28:40.109 --> 28:42.503
Hang in there, man.Thanks, man.

28:42.503 --> 28:45.941
I mean, out here, I don't mind
people knowing me.

28:45.941 --> 28:48.596
But I am themost hated man
from west to east

28:48.596 --> 28:50.467
for a whole lot of fools.

28:50.467 --> 28:54.297
It's like, you got popped,
you gotta be guilty, you know?

28:54.297 --> 28:56.473
I hear ya.

28:56.473 --> 28:59.433
Not much I can do
for your look, though.

28:59.433 --> 29:00.956
You can just shave it off.

29:00.956 --> 29:04.133
Huh.
That'll make Rainelle happy.

29:04.133 --> 29:06.919
[ Exhales ]You know she likes it clean.

29:06.919 --> 29:09.399
Uh-huh. It's true what they say
about you and her,

29:09.399 --> 29:11.053
back in the day?

29:11.053 --> 29:12.707
[ Laughs ] Come on now.Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

29:12.707 --> 29:14.535
Don't do that. Don't do that.All right. [ Laughs ]

29:14.535 --> 29:17.103
[ Laughs ] Me and her...

29:17.103 --> 29:20.846
we too old to remember
that far back anyhow.

29:20.846 --> 29:24.545
[ Laughter,
indistinct conversations ]

29:24.545 --> 29:28.331
Hey, Hal, you, um...

29:28.331 --> 29:30.029
think I could maybe use your car
for, like, an hour,

29:30.029 --> 29:31.770
after you finish me up?

29:31.770 --> 29:35.034
Sure thing.

29:44.347 --> 29:47.786
Back door. He's moving south
out of the alley. Pick me up.

29:59.188 --> 30:02.191
[ Man shouting indistinctly ]

30:14.464 --> 30:16.684
[ Shifts gears,
turns off engine ]

30:16.684 --> 30:20.557
♪♪

30:20.557 --> 30:22.168
You think it's a meet?

30:22.168 --> 30:23.734
Well, he ain't here for
fresh air and exercise.

30:23.734 --> 30:25.562
[ Window whirs ]

30:40.360 --> 30:43.972
[ Lowered voice ]
No, let's just hold back, okay?Mm-hmm.

31:01.555 --> 31:04.558
[ Indistinct conversations ]

31:24.752 --> 31:26.101
We can't follow him
in there.

31:26.101 --> 31:28.147
How long are we gonna wait?

31:29.931 --> 31:31.193
[ Two gunshots ]

31:31.193 --> 31:32.847
[ Women scream ]

31:32.847 --> 31:34.631
[ Dog barking in distance ]

31:34.631 --> 31:39.985
[ Woman screaming ]

31:39.985 --> 31:42.248
Wait, wait, wait!Go around, go around.

31:42.248 --> 31:46.817
♪♪

32:06.011 --> 32:08.056
Did you see the shooter?No. You?

32:08.056 --> 32:09.971
I was 20 seconds away.

32:09.971 --> 32:12.278
[ Panting ]

32:12.278 --> 32:15.672
He must've been on a bike.

32:15.672 --> 32:18.153
[ Holsters gun ]Ugh.

32:18.153 --> 32:19.763
This had to be a set-up.

32:19.763 --> 32:21.200
Right.
I'm gonna call it in.

32:21.200 --> 32:22.636
[ Keypad beeps ]

32:22.636 --> 32:28.642
[ Exhales ] You could've
just stayed in jail.

32:28.642 --> 32:32.254
There's no wallet, no phone.
It could be a robbery.

32:32.254 --> 32:34.387
Except the victim let the
shooter get in good and close

32:34.387 --> 32:35.736
from the powder burns.

32:35.736 --> 32:38.652
So you think he knew him?

32:38.652 --> 32:41.611
It's a reasonable assumption.
There's no defensive wounds.

32:41.611 --> 32:43.570
I also think
that the shooter --

32:43.570 --> 32:46.225
and this is just my
preliminary observation now.Okay.

32:46.225 --> 32:48.923
But from the angle of entry
and exit wounds,

32:48.923 --> 32:50.403
the shooter was
of a certain height

32:50.403 --> 32:52.535
and most likely male.

32:52.535 --> 32:53.928
All right. Thanks.

32:53.928 --> 32:56.235
Terry.

32:56.235 --> 32:57.671
[ Clears throat ] Sir.How did this happen?

32:57.671 --> 32:59.412
Uh, to be honest,
I-I don't know.

32:59.412 --> 33:01.370
We, uh, we were forced
to fall back.

33:01.370 --> 33:03.024
Our prime suspect
gets himself killed

33:03.024 --> 33:06.636
whilewe're tailing him?Yes, sir.

33:06.636 --> 33:09.944
[ Scoffs ] What a shitshow.

33:09.944 --> 33:12.077
[ Exhales sharply ]

33:12.077 --> 33:13.556
Do you have a theory?

33:13.556 --> 33:15.689
Uh, well, at this point,
we think he was laid out

33:15.689 --> 33:18.518
by the same cat that hired him
to kill Normandy Parker.

33:18.518 --> 33:20.650
Um...

33:20.650 --> 33:22.174
other than that, I --

33:22.174 --> 33:24.524
Oh, okay. Thanks for
that insight, Inspector.

33:24.524 --> 33:26.308
Lieutenant.

33:26.308 --> 33:27.875
We need to notify
the next of kin

33:27.875 --> 33:31.096
before they see it
on the news.

33:31.096 --> 33:33.011
Excuse me.

33:33.011 --> 33:34.751
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

33:34.751 --> 33:37.319
[ Lowered voice ]
Thank you.

33:37.319 --> 33:40.235
[ Indistinct conversations,
camera shutter clicking ]

33:44.587 --> 33:45.893
I hate this part.

33:45.893 --> 33:48.156
Yeah. Every time.

33:48.156 --> 33:51.638
You good?Yeah.

33:51.638 --> 33:53.118
[ Dog barks ]

33:53.118 --> 33:56.773
[ Gate squeaks ]

33:56.773 --> 34:01.735
First Normandy, now Billy.
[ Chuckles ]

34:01.735 --> 34:04.825
My two boys.

34:04.825 --> 34:07.915
They were like sons to me.

34:12.876 --> 34:16.054
Ms. James,
do you recall, uh...

34:16.054 --> 34:19.274
Billy saying he was going
to visit anyone?

34:19.274 --> 34:22.712
Going to meet up
with anyone?

34:22.712 --> 34:26.629
Did he suffer?

34:26.629 --> 34:29.763
You can tell me that much.

34:34.898 --> 34:37.988
No, ma'am.

34:37.988 --> 34:39.947
It was instant.

34:42.993 --> 34:47.476
Youmade him a target,

34:47.476 --> 34:50.697
the police,
with false accusations.

34:50.697 --> 34:55.223
He was the easiest answer
you had,

34:55.223 --> 34:59.097
and you were wrong.

34:59.097 --> 35:03.057
Ma'am, any information that you
may have could possibly help us

35:03.057 --> 35:04.537
figure out who murdered him.

35:04.537 --> 35:07.148
[ Chuckles ]
Well, look in the mirror.

35:07.148 --> 35:09.194
That's who killed Billy.

35:11.848 --> 35:15.069
He'd still be alive
if it wasn't for y'all.

35:18.768 --> 35:22.032
So you can get up
off my couch

35:22.032 --> 35:28.474
and walk yourselves out
my front door.

35:28.474 --> 35:30.215
Well, if anything should
occur to you,

35:30.215 --> 35:31.825
you know where
you can find us.

35:31.825 --> 35:37.613
[ Chuckles ] Like your
black skin makes us family.

35:37.613 --> 35:39.963
Well, it doesn't.

35:39.963 --> 35:42.096
Don't litter my table up
with your mess.

35:42.096 --> 35:44.751
Take it with you.
I don't want it.

35:44.751 --> 35:46.883
[ Telephone rings ]

35:46.883 --> 35:49.973
People already hearing
the news.

35:49.973 --> 35:51.453
[ Ring ]

35:51.453 --> 35:54.195
We're very sorry
for your loss, ma'am.

35:54.195 --> 35:56.284
God's gain.

35:56.284 --> 35:58.852
[ Ringing continues ]

35:58.852 --> 36:01.246
Would you, uh...

36:01.246 --> 36:05.641
mind closing the blinds
on your way out so...

36:05.641 --> 36:07.730
[ Voice breaks ] so people
won't see me like this?

36:07.730 --> 36:09.341
Of course.

36:13.040 --> 36:14.911
[ Blinds rattle ]

36:18.219 --> 36:21.483
[ Footsteps depart,
door closes ]

36:28.534 --> 36:31.972
[ Inhales sharply ]

36:36.542 --> 36:39.066
Hey, Cass, uh...
it's me. Just got home.

36:39.066 --> 36:41.111
Just wanted to say I miss you.[ Knocks on door ]

36:41.111 --> 36:42.939
I'm gonna call back.

36:42.939 --> 36:44.637
[ Dog barking in distance,
phone beeps ]

36:44.637 --> 36:46.029
[ Sighs ]

36:46.029 --> 36:47.335
Who is it?

36:47.335 --> 36:48.945
It's Martin.[ Sighs heavily ]

36:50.773 --> 36:52.035
[ Sighs ]

36:57.476 --> 36:59.478
You know what?
I tried to warn you, Marty.

36:59.478 --> 37:01.393
I'm sorry you didn't listen.[ Door closes ]

37:01.393 --> 37:04.134
You know, I came by to tell you
I know what you did, Mario.

37:04.134 --> 37:06.311
I knowyou leaked the file
to the defense.

37:06.311 --> 37:07.703
I know you did.

37:07.703 --> 37:09.836
[ Decanter clatters ]

37:09.836 --> 37:11.577
Are you out of your mind?

37:11.577 --> 37:13.840
It's the only way she could've
known! It's the only way!

37:13.840 --> 37:16.321
I would never damage
the office like that.

37:16.321 --> 37:18.975
I've devoted my life
to that office.

37:18.975 --> 37:20.890
I told you this thing was
discoverable.

37:20.890 --> 37:22.675
And if you hadn't been --You're a liar!

37:22.675 --> 37:25.895
You're lying, just like you lied
about how you killed that nurse.

37:25.895 --> 37:28.985
Mm-hmm. I saw how much you were
drinking that night. I saw it!

37:28.985 --> 37:31.205
Marty --Don't touch me!

37:34.600 --> 37:36.515
You know, you're never gonna
be a leader...

37:36.515 --> 37:38.212
[ Exhales deeply ]...if you underestimate
your enemies

37:38.212 --> 37:42.303
and undervalue your allies.

37:42.303 --> 37:44.827
I don't benefit
from your failure, Marty.

37:44.827 --> 37:47.221
I handpicked you.

37:47.221 --> 37:50.616
I believed in you.

37:50.616 --> 37:51.878
I still do.

37:51.878 --> 37:53.183
[ Sighs ]

37:53.183 --> 37:58.058
Marty, mistakes get made.

37:58.058 --> 38:00.321
True, you are gonna lose
this case...

38:00.321 --> 38:04.891
[ Exhales deeply ]But you will survive.

38:04.891 --> 38:06.545
Go home.

38:06.545 --> 38:08.155
Take a shower.

38:10.026 --> 38:12.115
Get naked with your wife.

38:14.727 --> 38:17.295
Okay?

38:17.295 --> 38:19.384
No apologies needed.

38:26.304 --> 38:28.262
You have a good night now.

38:30.873 --> 38:33.615
[ Door closes ]

38:33.615 --> 38:35.835
[ Mouth full ] 100%. 100%.Well, you have to meet her.

38:35.835 --> 38:38.359
That's okay, sweetie. I got it.
I know you have homework.

38:38.359 --> 38:41.841
Homework?
In the summertime? Mnh-mnh.

38:41.841 --> 38:44.931
It's an enrichment program.What? That is not cool.

38:44.931 --> 38:47.716
I hated doing homework
when I came up.

38:47.716 --> 38:49.152
See? He gets it.

38:49.152 --> 38:50.676
Thanks, Terry.Night, Lou.

38:50.676 --> 38:52.504
Night!

38:52.504 --> 38:55.202
I'm screwed
once she's a teenager.

38:55.202 --> 38:57.160
[ Inhales deeply ]Mm-hmm.

38:57.160 --> 39:01.164
I'm putting in for a transfer.What?

39:01.164 --> 39:03.906
Yeah. I figured
Special Investigations --No. Terry.

39:03.906 --> 39:08.215
No, you had a good idea.Stop, okay? I can't let you.

39:08.215 --> 39:10.652
I love you for offering. I do.
But we can't do this.

39:10.652 --> 39:13.481
Yes, we can.
We can, all right?

39:13.481 --> 39:15.440
We talked about
how we could make it work.

39:15.440 --> 39:17.442
Yeah, and we've been fighting
and it's been weird ever since.

39:17.442 --> 39:21.054
That's why I'm giving in.

39:23.099 --> 39:24.623
I can't let you, okay?

39:24.623 --> 39:26.886
I just...we can't do it,

39:26.886 --> 39:30.150
not like this.

39:30.150 --> 39:34.894
Look, I was thinking about
what you said,

39:34.894 --> 39:36.591
and you were right.

39:36.591 --> 39:39.594
It is easier, much easier for me
to make the change,

39:39.594 --> 39:41.901
so I'm gonna do it.

39:41.901 --> 39:44.425
[ Sighs deeply ]

39:44.425 --> 39:46.035
We're great partners.Mm-hmm.

39:46.035 --> 39:48.603
We make each other better cops.Mm-hmm.

39:48.603 --> 39:50.692
But if one of us
has to burn down a career,

39:50.692 --> 39:52.390
a year from now,

39:52.390 --> 39:54.261
we're not gonna be partners,
we're not gonna be lovers.

39:54.261 --> 39:57.307
We're not even gonna be friends.Whoa. Slow down. Slow down.

39:57.307 --> 39:59.353
That's -- that's bleak.

39:59.353 --> 40:01.529
Well, I'd rather have two out
of three than nothing at all.

40:01.529 --> 40:04.097
Well, what if we could have
three out of three?Sure, of course.

40:04.097 --> 40:05.751
But if we don't want what's best
for each other,

40:05.751 --> 40:09.494
then what's the point?

40:09.494 --> 40:11.800
I mean, do you really wanna do
Special Investigations?

40:11.800 --> 40:14.542
No, but I'm willing.
I'm willing to try.

40:14.542 --> 40:17.763
Okay, but that's
too much pressure on me.

40:17.763 --> 40:20.330
[ Inhales and exhales deeply ]

40:23.116 --> 40:25.205
If you transfer,

40:25.205 --> 40:29.339
everybody's gonna think
it's because of the shooting.

40:29.339 --> 40:31.777
It's not gonna be good
for the department.

40:31.777 --> 40:35.607
[ Sets down glass ]

40:35.607 --> 40:37.478
So then we're stuck,

40:37.478 --> 40:41.743
'cause we can't move forward
and I guess we can't go back.

40:41.743 --> 40:43.963
[ Sighs deeply ]

40:43.963 --> 40:46.966
I mean, I think we just
have to be...

40:46.966 --> 40:48.402
grownups.

40:48.402 --> 40:51.231
♪♪

40:51.231 --> 40:56.976
What is that?
Being sensible but sad?

40:56.976 --> 41:00.196
Come on. Admit it.

41:00.196 --> 41:03.635
Aren't you
a little relieved?

41:05.201 --> 41:08.466
We didn't become cops because
we're scared of the truth.

41:08.466 --> 41:13.166
♪♪

41:13.166 --> 41:14.384
You know, these dishes aren't
gonna do themselves.

41:14.384 --> 41:16.778
No, it's fine. I got it.

41:16.778 --> 41:18.476
You can go home.

41:18.476 --> 41:21.479
♪♪

41:38.408 --> 41:40.541
[ Door closes ]

41:44.414 --> 41:47.461
♪♪
